main event: A civilian observed a UFO in Ojibwa, Wisconsin on May 15, 1953.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 25 minutes,The conclusion of the report indicates that there was conflicting data regarding the sighting,The observation was made visually from the ground,The object was traveling east at an estimated speed of 120 mph,No physical evidence or photographs were obtained from the sighting.
witness description: Civilians, specifically identified as Bill Olsen and another individual
